HEADWORD: Electuary
<hw>E*lec"tu*a*ry</hw> <pr>(?; 135)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Electuaries</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[OE.
<ets>letuaire</ets>, OF. <ets>lettuaire</ets>, <ets>electuaire</ets>, F.
<ets>⟦eacute⟧lectuaire</ets>, L. <ets>electuarium</ets>,
<ets>electarium</ets>. prob. fr. Gr. <?/, <?/ a medicine that is licked
away, fr. Gr. <?/ to lick up; <grk>'ek</grk> out + <?/ to lick. See
<er>Lick</er>, and cf. <er>Eclegm</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A
